caption: I admire this place! They prepare tasty meals, their menu is nice, The cook in that restaurant is a real authority in the kitchen, I like very much trying all their dishes. The food is always fresh and tasty, the service towards the clients  is nice. I  go often to this restaurant and I not even once was discontended.  I highly recommend it.

I really wanted to love this place. It was clean and the service was pretty good but the pad see ew just wasn't anything to write home about. If you're looking for a mediocre Thai restaurant this will fix your craving, if you're looking for spectacular, this just ain’t it.
It's a fantastic place to go for lunch or a casual dinner. The food is well cooked and delicious. The atmosphere is charming. Service is great.
This spot is worth a visit. They serve big portions for reasonable rates. Regularly clean and with fantastic atmosphere. Would recommend to others.
Food was delivered without any rice to accompany. Shame
Hands down Best Tom Yum soup in IL. Just a perfect amount of every ingredient. I also tried Pineapple rice and it was great as well. Will be coming back to try more food here.
Ordered green curry via DoorDash but received without rice. It’s extra. I don’t think I’ve ever been to a Thai restaurant that charges extra for rice. Send kinda cheap and greedy don’t you think?

I cannot begin to share how much I love the food at this place. I have ordered so many times from this place, specially during the COVID situation.  They do take out orders and the order is ready to be picked up within minutes. Never had any trouble and always had an amazing experience. It is one of my favorite restaurants in Chicago.
Thai food and the setting at this place is super good. Normally I would have posted a pic but food looked so good I couldn't stop. I will be bringing family next time. The bill was fair.

We've ordered from them many times, and Dao Thai has always been great for us!  -They've never once messed up an order. -The food is always delicious -The food is available for pickup when they say it will be -They are able to provide vegan/vegetarian options for most of their curries, papaya salad, etc  We've tried other Thai restaurants in the city, but will stick with Dao.

I've ordered twice during the pandemic so far. The first time I ordered two Lao tables on a Saturday & the second time was today, Mother's Day, when I ordered one Lao table. The first time, picking up the food was effortless. There was plenty of parking in front, and I got my food in less than 2 minutes.
Love this place!
Sooo good, nice room
The pad see eiw was probably the best I've had in my life. Almost seems like they use honey in the recipe for the sauce instead of sugar. I loved it!

My husband and I came across this place one night when we were looking for a place to eat.  The staff were friendly and they took our orders right away.  The food came out quickly and it was huge portions!  Everything tasted great and we really enjoyed the decor and seating.  If you’re looking for some Thai food and friendly service this was a great place to go!  We were here June 2019 when we stayed in Chicago for a few days.

I've been a frequent guest to Dao Thai over the years and I have three words - Thai Done Right. Welcomed with big smiles by the staff, Dao's food is equally inviting with the usual delicious Thai favorites seasoned perfectly. Try the Mussman Curry. Vegan friendly with a quant patio and lightning fast, accurate takeout or delivered to your door. A+++ and a true neighborhood favorite, my only complaint is they won't part with one of ornate wooden canines that anchor the dining room with it's authentic Thai atmosphere.
Great place for tasty thai food. i love snacking here. the service was very helpful and welcoming. prices were fair.
Thai food, super tasty. Loved this place from the first taste. This place has an awesome feel to it.
Nice staff and good food, quickly made. I recommend this restaurant.
Great food, nice servers, and amazing decor. The mango smoothie is bomb 😍😍
Always a cozy and good time. Fav meals here mango bubble tea, chicken rice soup so good!

This is absolutely my FAVORITE restaurant! I've been eating here for 15 years and have never, not once, had a bad meal. There is nothing like a mango or lychee martini and ginger chicken on the lovely patio in the summer. I've introduced many friends to this place, who now claim it as their own favorite. I've brought my parents here, and they request it when visiting from the suburbs. It's such a humble, authentic place and you can taste the love in every dish. I can honestly say that I recommend everything! You just can't go wrong here!
Just ok

I celebrated my birthday earlier this evening in this fine place. Well we had a superb evening and the venue was evidently one of the reasons for this strong evening. The team  cooperated in a pleasant manner, the meals were yummy and my friends were very  cheerful. We shall surely come back again for more celebrations. Thank you very much.

Very elegant and convenient spot. They provide big meals and for economical rates. We enjoyed the food a lot and the staff members were very friendly and informative. Will definitely recommend this place.

I go to this lovely place from time to time! This is the best place to grab a bite.  I visit this place many times. The meals are very tasty, the crew is friendly and the prices are affordable. I like meeting in this place for a rich lunch.
I love the atmosphere!! Everyone is so happy and upbeat.. The food is amazing!!
This place is awesome! Good rates, big portions and the staff are constantly welcoming.
Didn’t like the food, I visited this place with my family, we each tried one dish, so total of 4 dishes but didn’t like any.

The food is very filling and an entree can be split between 2 people easily. The entrees are served family style so they are easy to share. Be prepared though, they have the rice seperate from the entrees so you have to factor in the extra price of rice. But all in all, the food is delicious and worth the walk.

This restaurant was better in the past. We walked in at 1 pm and were sat immediately. We had to ask for lunch special menus because they were reluctant to offer us the lunch special rates (the special runs until 3!) The food was alright, less flavor than the previous owners put in their dishes. We order a large Tom Ka Kai soup to spend split. We have half the bowl of soup left when a waiter comes and asks if we are done. We told them we are still working on it and they promptly put dirty plates into the soup bowl and take it away, guess it doesn't matter what the customer wants. Later in the service, someone came to fill our water glasses and spilled the pitcher of water all over one of our guest's clothes. Accidents happen but there was ice and water all in our pad thai. They cleaned up and cleared the wet dishes. Then they came with the bill, full price, no discounts. So we asked for the rest of the soup we asked them to leave that they took away anyway. The waiter claimed it was thrown out (not my fault). So we left with no care from staff and one person went into the 34 degree weather with soaking wet clothes. We will choose one of the many Thai restaurants on that street from now on. Sad to see quality go down.

This restaurant is my favored. I go to plenty of restaurants but to this one I  constantly return again and again. The crew is very attentive and the cuisine they offer is so appetizing. I would always prefer to have a good dinner here. Highly recommended.
Thai food, yeah, yummy. staff is always super even when they have a full house. the service here is great. the place has an awesome atmosphere. food is similar to a place in san francisco i liked.
Superb environment and super amiable service. The menu was fresh and delightful. Will surely recommend this restaurant to others. Affordable prices and big portions. Keep it up.

Atmosphere is great, food is standard Thai, nothing to drive out of your way for, but if you’re in the area and are craving some Thai, it’s not a bad place.

Place is pretty decent. A lot of wait staff here and service was jus ok. At times they would just be conversing amongst themselves and not really paying attention to the few customers they had to tend to. The food was ok. The cucumber salad was a bit on the bland and water side. The thai tea deluxe was way too sweet that it tasted a bit gross to me. The ceazy spicy noodles was pretty good. You get the one shrimp just like the description says, front and center. The noodles had great flavor. The bean sprouts weren't cooked with the noodles for some reason, and just placed on top... usually you do that with noodle soup so it cooks in the broth. Pricing was good. Over all pretty average thai joint.
Found a good thai spot in Chicago it was some good food

Food - pretty good, though we utilized the tray with the chili sauces, crushed peanuts, and soy to add some flavor due to blandness Portions - terrific for the price! Left full, even without an appetizer Drinks - Tsingtao 👍❤ Service - fast, but came across rushed. We were one of four tables at the time (late Saturday night), and they were prepping to close an hour before their closing time. The hostess said two things when we were seated: welcome, and let us know when you're ready because the kitchen is closing. Again, this was 70 minutes prior to closing. Just sayin....  The bill was cheap and the atmosphere was warm and fun. There are better Thai places around though....particularly one "cozy" place a short train ride north.

Another "Green Curry review"... yes, I always review after trying green curry at Thai restaurants.  I enjoyed this green curry; however, it was listed on the menu as "Beef Green Curry", which I normally get the chicken, and I was not offered an ability to substitute, so, I rode it out.  The flavor of the curry, itself was creamy, and had a nice kick to it (I may have drank what was left out of the bowl); however, the beef was a little tough, and I could imagine it having been a "leftover" type of beef - not bad, just not a beef I would crave.  Overall, I liked the meal, and I can see myself returning any time I am in the neighborhood.  Lunch: $16+ (Green Curry, side of rice and green tea)

I have to say this is the best Thai food I have ever had -- fresh and unusually flavorful.  I ordered what is essentially Pad Thai--but unlike any Pad Thai I have ever had, called Yaowaraj Noodle. Just a little spicy but it comes with a super spicy liquid you can augment the dish with.  I can't drink dairy, so they made my Thai Ice Tea with Coconut milk--delicious and not as sweet as those made with sweetened condensed milk.  We shared a couple small plates--one was a mushroom curried mousse spread that came with rice crackers and the other was a yummy bean dish.  My friends had the chicken fat rice with Chicken, and both loved the dish.

Not to mention the sake which tasted of water with nail varnish remover, especially concerning was the fact that the bottle wasn't opened in front of us so nail varnish is a legitimate possibility. I don't usually leave reviews online but really, this warrants the warning. So unhappy with our choice.
